This is the template for encoding the left side of a tropical cyclone statistics table line, including the new row start.

== Usage ==

The invoking syntax of this template is <nowiki>{{TC stats cyclone|cat=|name=|dates=|max-winds=|min-press=|areas|damage=|deaths=}}</nowiki>.

:* ''cat'' must be a value from the left-side column of the following table
::{{TC stats cat doc table}}
:* ''name'' is the name/designation of the storm 
:** Do not include qualifiers such as "Hurricane" in the name.  For example, for the 11th named storm of the [[2005 Atlantic hurricane season]], this parameter should read "Katrina", '''not''' "Hurricane Katrina".)
:* ''dates'' is the active date range of the storm. 
:**The suggested format is "Month day1 - day2" 
:** When a storm starts and ends in different month, the suggested syntax is "Month1 day1 - Month2 day2".
:* ''max-winds'' is the maximum winds in miles per hour with kilometres per hour in parentheses.
:* ''min-press'' is the minimum pressure in millibars.
:* ''areas'' denotes the countries and/or regions affected by the storm. If no areas are affected by the storm, use ''areas=None''. Countries that the storm makes landfall in should be marked in '''bold'''.
* ''damage'' is the amount of damage done by the cyclone is millions of US dollars.
* ''deaths'' is the number of deaths caused by the cyclone.

For a full descption of how this template is used in conjunction with other [[:category:tropical cyclone statistics templates|tropical cyclone statistics templates]], see [[:template:TC stats table start3]].
